==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Derangement
<hw>De*range"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧rangement</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of deranging or
putting out of order, or the state of being deranged; disarrangement;
disorder; confusion; especially, mental disorder; insanity.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Disorder; confusion; embarrassment; irregularity;
disturbance; insanity; lunacy; madness; delirium; mania. See
<er>Insanity</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deranger</ent>⟦br⟧
